---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Link from '../components/Link.astro';
import TableOfContents from '../components/TableOfContents.astro';
const title = 'Map Theme - Cities Skylines Modding';
import { Picture } from 'astro:assets';
import { images } from '../data/imageImports.js';
---

<MainLayout title={title}>
	<TableOfContents />
	<section class="pt-12 pb-48 text-lg sm:ml-64 xl:mr-64 text-hit-gray-500">
		<h1 id="overview" class="pb-8 text-4xl font-bold border-b-4 border-hit-gray-600 text-hit-gray-400">
			Map Theme
		</h1>
		<div class="content">
			<h2
				class="pb-8 mt-24 text-4xl font-medium border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 text-hit-gray-400"
				id="environment"
			>
				<a
					href="#environment"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Environment</a
				>
			</h2>
			<p class="mt-4">
				Affects the cubemap which is visible in the water and highly specular asset reflections. Also affects
				the availability of some environment-specific vanilla assets.
			</p>
			<h2
				class="pb-8 mt-24 text-4xl font-medium border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 text-hit-gray-400"
				id="terrain-properties"
			>
				<a
					href="#terrain-properties"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Terrain Properties</a
				>
			</h2>
			<h3 class="pb-4 mt-16 text-2xl font-semibold border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-500" id="textures">
				<a
					href="#textures"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Textures</a
				>
			</h3>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="folder"
			>
				<a
					href="#folder"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Folder</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">The folder where you should put the textures for importing is located here:</p>
			<p class="mt-4">
				<span class="path">%LocalAppData%\Colossal Order\Cities_Skylines\Addons\ThemeEditor\ThemeTextures</span>
			</p>
			<p class="mt-4">
				The AppData folder is hidden by default, you can access it by copying and pasting the path into the file
				explorer, or pressing

				<span class="key">Windows + R</span> and typing in appdata.
			</p>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="resolution"
			>
				<a
					href="#resolution"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Resolution</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Map theme textures are usually 1024x1024, 2048x2048 or 4096x4096.</p>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="format"
			>
				<a
					href="#format"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Format</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Use a lossless format like .PNG.</p>
			<p class="mt-4">
				The game supports other formats as well, but there is no reason to use another one, it doesn't matter
				how much your texture is compressed or even if it's completely solid or complicated, the game will
				convert it to a DXT format, so the final size won't be affected by anything other than resolution.
			</p>
			<p class="mt-4">
				Make sure the texture is 8 bits/channel because a 16 bits/channel image can't be imported. Do not use
				the "Smaller File (8-bit)" feature in the Photoshop Export As window, as that creates an indexed color
				image, not an 8 bits/channel one.
			</p>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="grass"
			>
				<a
					href="#grass"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Grass</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">
				The main texture of grass, transparency controls how much the grass texture is affected by the grass
				color offsets.
			</p>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="ruined"
			>
				<a
					href="#ruined"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Ruined</a
				>
			</h4>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-6 mt-4 lg:flex-row">
				<div class="lg:w-2/3">
					<p>
						Appears near buildings, some props, networks, and hills which are not steep enough for the cliff
						texture to be visible. Also visible near pavement surface and can also be painted using surface
						painter. Also visible under sand, if the opacity of the sand texture is low enough. The opacity
						is usually very high.
					</p>
				</div><div class="lg:w-1/3">
					<a href="/images/theme/ruined.jpg" target="_blank">
						<Picture
							width={images.ruined.width / 3}
							densities={[1.5, 2]}
							formats={['avif', 'webp']}
							src={images.ruined}
							alt="Example of ruined texture"
							class="w-full h-auto"
							loading="eager"
						/></a
					><p class="explanation">Example of ruined texture.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="cliff"
			>
				<a
					href="#cliff"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Cliff</a
				>
			</h4>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-6 mt-4 lg:flex-row">
				<div class="lg:w-2/3">
					<p>Visible if the terrain is steep enough. Usually high opacity.</p>
				</div><div class="lg:w-1/3">
					<a href="/images/theme/cliff.jpg" target="_blank">
						<Picture
							width={images.cliff.width / 3}
							densities={[1.5, 2]}
							formats={['avif', 'webp']}
							src={images.cliff}
							alt="Example of cliff texture"
							class="w-full h-auto"
						/></a
					><p class="explanation">Example of cliff texture.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="cliff-normal"
			>
				<a
					href="#cliff-normal"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Cliff Normal</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">
				Adds bump to the cliff texture. <Link
					classes=""
					href="/normal-maps/"
					text="Requires a flipped green channel compared to the normal map standard"
					theme="internallink"
				/>.
			</p>
			<h4 class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12" id="sand">
				<a
					href="#sand"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Sand</a
				>
			</h4>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-6 mt-4 lg:flex-row">
				<div class="lg:w-2/3">
					<p>
						Can be painted. If the opacity is low, the ruined texture might be visible before the sand
						becomes fully visible. Can't coexist with the fertile color.
					</p>
				</div><div class="lg:w-1/3">
					<a href="/images/theme/sand.jpg" target="_blank">
						<Picture
							width={images.sand.width / 3}
							densities={[1.5, 2]}
							formats={['avif', 'webp']}
							src={images.sand}
							alt="Example of sand texture"
							class="w-full h-auto"
						/></a
					><p class="explanation">Example of sand texture.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="sand-normal"
			>
				<a
					href="#sand-normal"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Sand Normal</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">
				Adds bump to the sand texture. <Link
					classes=""
					href="/normal-maps/"
					text="Requires a flipped green channel compared to the normal map standard"
					theme="internallink"
				/>.
			</p>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="pavement"
			>
				<a
					href="#pavement"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Pavement</a
				>
			</h4>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-6 mt-4 lg:flex-row">
				<div class="lg:w-2/3">
					<p>
						Appears as surface paint on buildings, networks, or when painted using surface painter. Also can
						appear on network bridges using the bridge shader.
					</p>
				</div><div class="lg:w-1/3">
					<a href="/images/theme/pavement.jpg" target="_blank">
						<Picture
							width={images.pavement.width / 2}
							densities={[1.5, 2]}
							formats={['avif', 'webp']}
							src={images.pavement}
							alt="Example of pavement texture"
							class="w-full h-auto"
						/></a
					><p class="explanation">Example of pavement texture.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="gravel"
			>
				<a
					href="#gravel"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Gravel</a
				>
			</h4>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-6 mt-4 lg:flex-row">
				<div class="lg:w-2/3">
					<p>
						Appears as surface paint on buildings, networks, or when painted using surface painter. Also can
						appear on network bridges using the rail shader.
					</p>
				</div><div class="lg:w-1/3">
					<a href="/images/theme/gravel.jpg" target="_blank">
						<Picture
							width={images.gravel.width / 2}
							densities={[1.5, 2]}
							formats={['avif', 'webp']}
							src={images.gravel}
							alt="Example of gravel texture"
							class="w-full h-auto"
						/></a
					><p class="explanation">Example of gravel texture.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<h4 class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12" id="oil">
				<a
					href="#oil"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Oil</a
				>
			</h4>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-6 mt-4 lg:flex-row">
				<div class="lg:w-2/3">
					<p>
						Can be painted using the resource brush. Half-transparent by default, unless it's very bright.
						Can't coexist with ore.
					</p>
				</div><div class="lg:w-1/3">
					<a href="/images/theme/oilore.jpg" target="_blank">
						<Picture
							width={images.oilore.width / 2}
							densities={[1.5, 2]}
							formats={['avif', 'webp']}
							src={images.oilore}
							alt="Example of oil and ore texture"
							class="w-full h-auto"
						/></a
					><p class="explanation">Example of oil and ore textures.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<h4 class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12" id="ore">
				<a
					href="#ore"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Ore</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">
				Can be painted using the resource brush. Half-transparent by default, unless it's very bright. Can't
				coexist with oil
			</p>
			<h3
				class="pb-4 mt-16 text-2xl font-semibold border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-500"
				id="grass-color-offsets"
			>
				<a
					href="#grass-color-offsets"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Grass Color Offsets</a
				>
			</h3>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-6 mt-4 lg:flex-row">
				<div class="lg:w-2/3">
					<p>Colors which affect the grass texture based on its opacity.</p>
				</div><div class="lg:w-1/3">
					<a href="/images/theme/colors.jpg" target="_blank">
						<Picture
							width={images.colors.width / 2}
							densities={[1.5, 2]}
							formats={['avif', 'webp']}
							src={images.colors}
							alt="Example of color offsets"
							class="w-full h-auto"
						/></a
					><p class="explanation">Example of color offsets.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="pollution"
			>
				<a
					href="#pollution"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Pollution</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Appears where there is ground pollution.</p>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="field"
			>
				<a
					href="#field"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Field</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Appears as surface paint on buildings, or when painted using surface painter.</p>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="fertility"
			>
				<a
					href="#fertility"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Fertility</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Appears when painted using the fertile resource brush. Can't coexist with sand.</p>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="forest"
			>
				<a
					href="#forest"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Forest</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Appears where there are trees.</p>
			<h3
				class="pb-4 mt-16 text-2xl font-semibold border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-500"
				id="geometry-details"
			>
				<a
					href="#geometry-details"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Geometry Details</a
				>
			</h3>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-6 mt-4 lg:flex-row">
				<div class="lg:w-2/3">
					<p>2D sprites which are visible on the terrain.</p>
				</div><div class="lg:w-1/3">
					<a href="/images/theme/sprites.jpg" target="_blank">
						<Picture
							width={images.sprites.width / 2}
							densities={[1.5, 2]}
							formats={['avif', 'webp']}
							src={images.sprites}
							alt="Example of sprites"
							class="w-full h-auto"
						/></a
					><p class="explanation">Example of sprites.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="grass-1"
			>
				<a
					href="#grass-1"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Grass</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Visible on normal grass.</p>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="fertile"
			>
				<a
					href="#fertile"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Fertile</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Visible on fertile resource paint.</p>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="rocks"
			>
				<a
					href="#rocks"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Rocks</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Visible on cliffs and gravel.</p>
			<h2
				class="pb-8 mt-24 text-4xl font-medium border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 text-hit-gray-400"
				id="water-properties"
			>
				<a
					href="#water-properties"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Water Properties</a
				>
			</h2>
			<h3
				class="pb-4 mt-16 text-2xl font-semibold border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-500"
				id="textures-1"
			>
				<a
					href="#textures-1"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Textures</a
				>
			</h3>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="water-normal"
			>
				<a
					href="#water-normal"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Water Normal</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Constantly fades between the normal and a flipped and rotated version.</p>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="water-foam"
			>
				<a
					href="#water-foam"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Water Foam</a
				>
			</h4>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-6 mt-4 lg:flex-row">
				<div class="lg:w-2/3">
					<p>
						The red channel controls the normal foam when the water is moving. The green channel controls
						the foam on polluted water. It's safe to import a simple black &amp; white foam texture.
					</p>
				</div><div class="lg:w-1/3">
					<a href="/images/theme/watertextures.jpg" target="_blank">
						<Picture
							width={images.watertextures.width / 2}
							densities={[1.5, 2]}
							formats={['avif', 'webp']}
							src={images.watertextures}
							alt="Example of water normal and foam"
							class="w-full h-auto"
						/></a
					><p class="explanation">Example of water normal and foam.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<h3
				class="pb-4 mt-16 text-2xl font-semibold border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-500"
				id="water-colors"
			>
				<a
					href="#water-colors"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Water Colors</a
				>
			</h3>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="clean"
			>
				<a
					href="#clean"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Clean</a
				>
			</h4>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-6 mt-4 lg:flex-row">
				<div class="lg:w-2/3"><p>Deep water.</p></div><div class="lg:w-1/3">
					<a href="/images/theme/watercolors.jpg" target="_blank">
						<Picture
							width={images.watercolors.width / 2}
							densities={[1.5, 2]}
							formats={['avif', 'webp']}
							src={images.watercolors}
							alt="Example of water colors"
							class="w-full h-auto"
						/></a
					><p class="explanation">Example of water colors.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="dirty"
			>
				<a
					href="#dirty"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Dirty</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Polluted water.</p>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="underwater"
			>
				<a
					href="#underwater"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Underwater</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Shallow water.</p>
			<h2
				class="pb-8 mt-24 text-4xl font-medium border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 text-hit-gray-400"
				id="atmosphere-properties"
			>
				<a
					href="#atmosphere-properties"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Atmosphere Properties</a
				>
			</h2>
			<h3 class="pb-4 mt-16 text-2xl font-semibold border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-500" id="sun">
				<a
					href="#sun"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Sun</a
				>
			</h3>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="longitude-latitude"
			>
				<a
					href="#longitude-latitude"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Longitude &amp; Latitude</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Placement of the sun.</p>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
